      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "In-scope domain: non-cannulated Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw constructs under quasi-static F1717 loading",
      "description": "Model is applicable to non-cannulated Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw constructs with outer diameter 7.0–8.0 mm, rod diameter 5.5–6.0 mm CoCr or Ti alloy, tested under quasi-static ASTM F1717 compression-bending at displacement rates 1–5 mm/min. Excludes cannulated variants, dynamic fatigue loading, and implants with outer diameter outside 6.0–9.0 mm. Cortical and cancellous bone analogue blocks must conform to ASTM F1717 Appendix X1 density specifications."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "Operating envelope: F1717 quasi-static compression-bending bounds",
      "description": "Displacement rate: 1–5 mm/min; applied force range: 0–3500 N; construct axial offset: 45° ± 2° per ASTM F1717 §7.3; polyurethane block density: 0.16–0.32 g/cm³; temperature: 20–25 °C ambient; screw insertion torque: 4.0–6.0 N·m; rod pre-load: 0 N (no pre-stress applied). FEA mesh element size: 0.3–0.8 mm in screw thread region; contact friction coefficient: 0.20–0.35 (Ti-Ti interface)."
    }
  },
